# Use of Funds

The objective of this investment is to accelerate the transition from a validated research platform into a production-grade institutional intelligence infrastructure.

Capital will primarily be allocated to five strategic priorities.

---

## 1. Computational Infrastructure

Deploy dedicated computing infrastructure capable of operating BCSentinel continuously.

This includes dedicated blockchain infrastructure, high-performance compute resources and enterprise-grade storage required for permanent institutional monitoring.

The objective is to operate the platform continuously rather than through isolated research sessions.

---

## 2. Continuous Blockchain Intelligence

Ethereum currently processes several million transactions every day.

Rather than analysing every transaction, BCSentinel has been designed to investigate only the most relevant subset identified through its proprietary discovery methodology.

The next development stage targets continuous analysis of approximately **60,000–120,000 strategically selected transactions per day**, allowing the platform to identify candidate formation processes while maintaining computational efficiency.

As infrastructure expands, processing capacity can scale accordingly.

---

## 3. Advanced AI Infrastructure

Expand the reasoning capabilities supporting institutional investigations.

Future investment will support increasingly capable AI models dedicated to:

• evidence interpretation

• entity attribution

• institutional report generation

• knowledge extraction

• library expansion

• investigation assistance

Artificial intelligence is designed to augment empirical investigation.

Strategic decisions, platform evolution and methodological changes always remain under human supervision.

---

## 4. Product Development

Complete the transition from research environment to enterprise-grade institutional platform.

Development priorities include:

• investigation workflows

• continuous monitoring

• institutional reporting

• client platform

• enterprise security

• platform scalability

---

## 5. Institutional Deployment

Prepare BCSentinel for commercial deployment through pilot programmes, infrastructure hardening, documentation and strategic institutional partnerships.

The objective is to establish long-term relationships with a limited number of institutional organisations.

